1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:11,200
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,167
Every July, the hospital resets.

3
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:15,700
New residents, new chaos,

4
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:17,300
same nurses doing
damage control,

5
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,667
so July doesn't kill anybody.

6
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:23,100
Ugh.

7
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:25,033
Do you need a hand?

8
00:00:25,033 --> 00:00:27,767
Nope, I'm doing great.
All on my own, thank you!

9
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:30,133
Yeah, okay, I'm such a bad guy,

10
00:00:30,133 --> 00:00:33,500
daring to deliver your mom
eternal peace.

11
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:36,767
[NURSE]<i> Paging Dr. Godwin.
</i> Please come to Room Five...

12
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,600
You know, I don't think
she's going to be okay.

13
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:41,233
I can...

14
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:42,333
[SNIFFS]

15
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:44,767
I can smell her time
running out!

16
00:00:44,767 --> 00:00:46,600
[NOA] Shut up!

17
00:00:47,367 --> 00:00:48,733
I don't have time for this.

18
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,733
No time? Hmm?

19
00:00:54,367 --> 00:00:55,733
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

20
00:00:56,533 --> 00:01:01,133
[WHISTLING]

21
00:01:01,133 --> 00:01:03,133
[ELEVATOR THUDS]

22
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,500
Hm? Huh?

23
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:06,300
[GRIM] Oh, look at that.

24
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:08,633
Now we have all
the time in the world.

25
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:11,367
No one can escape
their fate, Noa.

26
00:01:12,167 --> 00:01:13,300
Sorry, Grim.

27
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:14,767
No one's dying on my watch.

28
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:18,767
[BELL RINGING]

29
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:24,733
[SIGHS]

30
00:01:27,133 --> 00:01:28,800
Hi, Phineas.

31
00:01:29,433 --> 00:01:30,667
Another new one.

32
00:01:31,733 --> 00:01:34,133
And why are you
making that face?

33
00:01:34,133 --> 00:01:35,733
With your history
of panic attacks,

34
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:38,200
keep that paper bag nearby

35
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,733
and you'll be
out of here in no time.

36
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:40,967
Thanks, Doctor.

37
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,333
But my son's getting
his first school award.

38
00:01:43,667 --> 00:01:46,300
- Can't miss it.
- Oh, and you won't.

39
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:47,833
Hey, Doc.

40
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:49,367
Can I talk to you for a second?

41
00:01:49,367 --> 00:01:50,400
Excuse us.

42
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:51,733
Hey, Doc.

43
00:01:52,433 --> 00:01:53,533
I looked at her records.

44
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:55,633
I think we should order
more tests-- [STAMMERS]

45
00:01:55,633 --> 00:01:58,500
Nurse, just increase the
dose of her anxiety meds.

46
00:01:58,500 --> 00:01:59,633
Yeah, but what if
it's something--

47
00:01:59,633 --> 00:02:00,767
Those are my orders.

48
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:01,733
[DOOR OPENS]

49
00:02:02,533 --> 00:02:03,667
Yes, Doc.

50
00:02:05,867 --> 00:02:07,433
- [SIGHS]
- [DOOR CLOSES]

51
00:02:10,467 --> 00:02:11,800
What are you doing?

52
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:12,833
I'm checking.

53
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:14,700
Did you say something?

54
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:16,833
[SIGHS]

55
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:20,433
Finny, did these feel like
any of your other attacks?

56
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:23,567
Well, yeah. I couldn't breathe.

57
00:02:24,467 --> 00:02:27,333
My chest got so tight.

58
00:02:27,333 --> 00:02:28,733
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

59
00:02:28,733 --> 00:02:30,533
I really just thought
I was going to die.

60
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,467
Anything else?

61
00:02:33,133 --> 00:02:34,100
[SIGHS]

62
00:02:34,467 --> 00:02:35,633
My back.

63
00:02:35,633 --> 00:02:37,400
It's like someone
stuck a knife in it.

64
00:02:39,433 --> 00:02:40,667
But it's better now.

65
00:02:41,333 --> 00:02:42,567
The pulse is thready.

66
00:02:43,533 --> 00:02:45,333
Wait, what are you doing?

67
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,833
This isn't tracking.

68
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:50,133
Wait... But the doctor said,
I'll be fine.

69
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:52,533
- Just give me a second.
- No, stop it.

70
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:54,500
- No, you're scaring me.
- I just need a second.

71
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:55,467
Listen to her, dear!

72
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:57,833
- No, I need to make sure.
- I said stop!

73
00:02:57,833 --> 00:02:59,467
Dear, let it go!

74
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:05,800
[SLOW, DEEP BREATHING]

75
00:03:07,667 --> 00:03:09,233
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

76
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:10,733
Whoa, whoa. Blink slower.

77
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:12,600
Those eyelashes
are causing a draft.

78
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:15,267
I am expecting a
high-profile company.

79
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:18,367
Relax. Not every moment
is a close-up, Princess Sarah.

80
00:03:18,367 --> 00:03:21,300
Should I clap too for every
progress note so you feel seen?

81
00:03:21,633 --> 00:03:22,567
[GASPS]

82
00:03:22,567 --> 00:03:24,900
- Here he is!
- Whoa, whoa, what now?

83
00:03:25,467 --> 00:03:28,433
The Director Marty is here.
And he's here for me!

84
00:03:28,433 --> 00:03:30,200
- Who?
- [MARTY] Camille.

85
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:32,800
Darling, long time no see.

86
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,400
- [CAMILLE] Hi.
- [SMOOCHES]

87
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,833
Hey, hey! You better
put that down,

88
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:37,433
or I'm going to turn
that into suppository.

89
00:03:37,433 --> 00:03:40,633
Ros, this is the Director Marty.

90
00:03:40,633 --> 00:03:42,767
He's a legend. I'm menopausal.
So what?

91
00:03:42,767 --> 00:03:44,633
Don't worry.
This will be private.

92
00:03:44,633 --> 00:03:45,667
That's what that
asshole said too.

93
00:03:45,667 --> 00:03:48,533
Now my nude is a wallpaper
in some groupchat.

94
00:03:48,533 --> 00:03:49,833
Ros, wait.

95
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:50,933
Excuse me.

96
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:52,200
What?

97
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:54,367
Get us a private room.

98
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,333
Private room? Try HIPAA.

99
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:57,833
- Ten dollars.
- 30.

100
00:03:57,833 --> 00:03:58,833
Twenty dollars.

101
00:03:58,833 --> 00:03:59,933
I'll prep your room.

102
00:04:01,633 --> 00:04:02,967
- [SQUEALS]
- [TELEPHONE RINGS]

103
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:05,867
Run the symptoms again.

104
00:04:05,867 --> 00:04:07,733
Maybe you're overthinking.

105
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:08,833
I'm not.

106
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,600
- Grim said...
- He's a liar.

107
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:14,333
Patients downplay things.

108
00:04:14,333 --> 00:04:15,833
Then talk to them.

109
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,933
She's already filed a complaint.

110
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:20,233
Then get help.

111
00:04:20,233 --> 00:04:22,333
Her attending isn't answering.

112
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,900
Well, he's still a doctor.

113
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:27,267
No. He's just a resident.

114
00:04:27,867 --> 00:04:29,267
You're smart, dear.

115
00:04:29,267 --> 00:04:32,733
But the clinical eye,
it takes decades.

116
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:34,900
I have a third eye.

117
00:04:35,533 --> 00:04:37,667
- Does that not count?
- Wow.

118
00:04:37,667 --> 00:04:39,233
She's funny now.

119
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,733
Okay, Miss Know-it-all.

120
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:45,267
With all of your experience,
what do you think it looks like?

121
00:04:53,867 --> 00:04:58,433
Half my patients with aortic
dissections were misdiagnosed.

122
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:05,967
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:09,900
So I wait...

124
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,833
She dies.

125
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:23,767
Here's your return
of the comeback.

126
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:25,500
For the art.

127
00:05:27,467 --> 00:05:30,267
But this HIPAA thing,
will it be a problem?

128
00:05:30,867 --> 00:05:31,800
Not at all.

129
00:05:36,633 --> 00:05:39,400
[KEYPAD CLACKS]

130
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:42,367
[CLOCK TICKING]

131
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:46,500
Dear, you're risking everything.

132
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:48,300
For what?

133
00:05:50,633 --> 00:05:52,700
A life, Mom.

134
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:55,667
[CLOCK TICKING CONTINUES]

135
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,767
[EXHALES DEEPLY] Not again.

136
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:00,433
Not on my watch.

137
00:06:02,467 --> 00:06:04,567
Ready to give your
audience your all?

138
00:06:05,633 --> 00:06:06,767
I'll save her.

139
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:09,900
- Whatever it takes.
- Whatever it takes.

140
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:20,567
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

141
00:06:20,567 --> 00:06:22,000
- [SHUSHING]
- Good morning, everyone.

142
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:26,767
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

143
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:28,033
That was weird.

144
00:06:30,767 --> 00:06:32,767
Hey, can we...

145
00:06:35,867 --> 00:06:38,467
Look, I know I'm not
supposed to be talking to you.

146
00:06:38,467 --> 00:06:40,433
But there's something
you should know.

147
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:41,433
What?

148
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:43,067
Who told you you
shouldn't be talking to me?

149
00:06:43,067 --> 00:06:44,467
My girlfriend.

150
00:06:44,467 --> 00:06:45,967
But that's not the point, Noa.

151
00:06:45,967 --> 00:06:48,000
People are talking,
and it is not good.

152
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,033
They're saying that

153
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:51,433
a patient is complaining
about you harassing her,

154
00:06:51,433 --> 00:06:53,933
and going against
Dr. Lee's orders.

155
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:55,833
I'm trying to save her life.

156
00:06:57,667 --> 00:07:00,000
Dude, I knew there was no way
that you were just going

157
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,767
to break the chain of command
like that or something.

158
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:08,000
Noa, 30 minutes, your office.

159
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,400
We have a certain
doctor to deal with.

160
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:12,100
Good morning.

161
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:13,067
Hmm.

162
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:26,467
You've come such a long way.

163
00:07:27,133 --> 00:07:28,100
Downward.

164
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:31,167
Before, you were unreachable.

165
00:07:31,167 --> 00:07:32,433
Hold still, please.

166
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,000
Now?

167
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:38,033
Beggar level project
in a hospital like this?

168
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:41,767
[KNOCKS]

169
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:44,000
Is it okay if I grab
something from here?

170
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,767
Do you know her?

171
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:48,933
Get out!

172
00:07:50,667 --> 00:07:53,567
[WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:56,200
Everything happens for a reason.

174
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,500
Babe, I'm not talking to her.

175
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,067
Why do you think I'm
jogging on my break?

176
00:08:03,067 --> 00:08:04,233
[WOMAN]<i> I know
</i> you're talking to her.

177
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:06,900
Oh, that's why you vanished.

178
00:08:07,567 --> 00:08:09,633
No one invited you, dude.
I gotta go, babe.

179
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:11,567
- [WOMAN]<i> Bye.
</i>- Yeah, but this is fun.

180
00:08:15,533 --> 00:08:17,800
[PANTS, GRUNTS]

181
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,633
- What are you, an Olympian?
- No.

182
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,900
I'm not watching naked
men fight for glory again.

183
00:08:22,933 --> 00:08:24,233
- Beat ya!
- What?

184
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:26,933
- Okay.
- Are you good?

185
00:08:26,933 --> 00:08:28,700
I don't like liars
or cheats, okay?

186
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,600
That's what Noa says.

187
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,233
Why? Is she talking about me?

188
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:34,967
[SCOFFS] Sycophant.

189
00:08:34,967 --> 00:08:36,733
Look, I'm not the one
who took my flowers

190
00:08:36,733 --> 00:08:37,867
and tried to give them to her.

191
00:08:37,867 --> 00:08:38,933
Then challenge me.

192
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:40,800
Like the Olympians.

193
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,733
If I win, you drop
the silent treatment.

194
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:45,933
Didn't think you cared
about what people thought?

195
00:08:45,933 --> 00:08:46,900
I don't.

196
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,633
I just hate unfinished business.

197
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:50,867
Deal?

198
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:52,800
- Deal.
- Alright then.

199
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:56,933
Whoa, whoa! Let's keep
the pants on for this one.

200
00:08:57,967 --> 00:08:58,967
Are you sure?

201
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:01,700
- Pretty sure.
- Alright.

202
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:06,533
One, two, three, go.

203
00:09:06,533 --> 00:09:07,633
[CHUCKLES]

204
00:09:09,067 --> 00:09:10,700
Did you check the vitals
for this patient?

205
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,133
- Yes.
- Okay, what about for her?

206
00:09:12,133 --> 00:09:14,800
Insubordination is
grounds for termination.

207
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:16,600
Slow down, doc.

208
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,167
Excuse us.

209
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:21,167
Excuse us.

210
00:09:22,533 --> 00:09:23,500
Jane.

211
00:09:25,533 --> 00:09:27,933
As I responded to your emails,

212
00:09:27,967 --> 00:09:31,833
we do not fire someone
over a single verbal complaint.

213
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:34,300
Don't ever mention
the troponin test.

214
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:36,967
I'm sorry, Dr. Lee.

215
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:39,767
I don't accept your apology.

216
00:09:39,767 --> 00:09:41,700
Here's what I do accept.

217
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:44,900
Nurses take vitals.
That's her scope.

218
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:47,667
I'm not firing someone
for doing her job.

219
00:09:47,667 --> 00:09:49,633
- Thank you.
- However,

220
00:09:49,633 --> 00:09:51,967
you will receive
a formal write-up.

221
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:55,133
You undermined a physician
in front of a patient.

222
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:56,667
I need better from you.

223
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:59,067
Your team needs better from you.

224
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:00,333
That's all?

225
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,867
I don't get a say in this?

226
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:05,000
You do, but in this lane,
the call is mine.

227
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:06,967
[SIGHS]

228
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:13,333
Just remember, when this
blows back, it lands on you.

229
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:18,767
[SIGHS]

230
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:24,300
I'm sorry for how that looked.

231
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:27,733
Don't be sorry. Be sure.

232
00:10:28,133 --> 00:10:30,000
If you're going to break ranks,

233
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,000
you better be
damn certain you're right.

234
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:34,300
I can't just sit here and
listen to someone die.

235
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,300
He's wrong.

236
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,100
There's something
you're not saying.

237
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:46,067
And if you lie to me,
I can't protect you.

238
00:10:46,867 --> 00:10:48,200
If the hospital finds out
about this,

239
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,800
you'll lose your license
forever.

240
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:53,100
It's nothing.

241
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:54,700
Thank you, Jane.

242
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:04,300
[JANE] Noa.

243
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:06,933
One last thing.

244
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:13,133
Your mom would have been proud

245
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:16,300
seeing you fight for
that patient like that.

246
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,800
[SILLY MUSIC PLAYING]

247
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,067
[GRUNTING]

248
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:35,133
Seventy-three?

249
00:11:35,133 --> 00:11:37,100
- That was seventy-one.
- [GRUNTS]

250
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:43,867
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

251
00:11:51,867 --> 00:11:53,800
There she is.

252
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,300
Our brave survivor.

253
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:56,400
Ready for your close-up?

254
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:59,333
Well, I can't stay long.

255
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:01,333
My son's getting an award.

256
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:02,833
Perfect.

257
00:12:02,833 --> 00:12:04,200
Motherhood guilt.

258
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,800
That's our emotional arc.

259
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,233
Here's $100 as agreed.

260
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:10,267
- Oh, thank you.
- Let's do BTS.

261
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:12,367
You're discharged.

262
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:14,433
So we can use you now.

263
00:12:14,467 --> 00:12:15,467
Right, Camille?

264
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:19,200
Let's move her to this chair.

265
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:22,400
Oh, okay. Hold on.

266
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,167
[GROANS]

267
00:12:25,467 --> 00:12:28,267
- [CAMILLE] Oh!
- [GROANING]

268
00:12:28,267 --> 00:12:31,100
- Are you sure you're okay?
- It's my back.

269
00:12:32,867 --> 00:12:34,433
This hundred will
make me feel better.

270
00:12:35,067 --> 00:12:37,900
At least I will have
enough for a congrats gift.

271
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:39,300
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

272
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,900
Camille, put your hand
on her back.

273
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:42,367
- Okay.
- Like you care.

274
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:45,000
- Oof...
- Oh, did that hurt?

275
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,367
It just... it moved.

276
00:12:46,367 --> 00:12:47,933
Chest to back.

277
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:49,733
It's weird, right?

278
00:12:50,767 --> 00:12:51,867
Cut!

279
00:12:52,467 --> 00:12:54,167
Be sadder!

280
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:56,233
Let's try this again.

281
00:12:57,300 --> 00:12:58,167
Action!

282
00:12:59,767 --> 00:13:01,267
Director, I can't.

283
00:13:01,267 --> 00:13:03,800
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:07,933
[FINNY BREATHING HEAVILY]

285
00:13:08,933 --> 00:13:09,833
Camille.

286
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:12,067
One more mistake...

287
00:13:12,533 --> 00:13:13,833
This is over.

288
00:13:14,767 --> 00:13:15,867
Do you understand?

289
00:13:17,867 --> 00:13:18,900
[SIGHS]

290
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,400
[FINNY GROANS]

291
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:30,900
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

292
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,000
[EXHALES SOFTLY]

293
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,233
Dear, don't.

294
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:38,267
[NOA] She's dissecting.

295
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:39,833
We're out of time.

296
00:13:44,033 --> 00:13:45,033
You guys, where's 503?

297
00:13:45,033 --> 00:13:47,100
- She's not in her room.
- I can look it up.

298
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:48,767
She's been discharged.

299
00:13:48,767 --> 00:13:50,900
No, she's taking a walk
with Camille.

300
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:51,933
[NOA] What?!

301
00:13:51,933 --> 00:13:53,133
She shouldn't be!

302
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:54,100
Huh?

303
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:56,233
W-Wait! Wait!

304
00:13:56,233 --> 00:13:59,833
[SOFT, TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

305
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:00,800
Stop!

306
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,533
Do you want us
to get kicked out of here?

307
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:04,000
Keep rolling.

308
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,133
Excuse me. Excuse me.

309
00:14:06,133 --> 00:14:07,067
Finny?

310
00:14:07,267 --> 00:14:08,133
Okay.

311
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:10,000
What is she doing here?

312
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:12,033
Finny, I need you
to stop moving.

313
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:13,033
I know you want to see your son,

314
00:14:13,033 --> 00:14:14,233
but if you walk out
those doors right now,

315
00:14:14,233 --> 00:14:16,600
you increase your chance
of dying every hour.

316
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:17,933
[CRYING]

317
00:14:17,933 --> 00:14:18,967
Director.

318
00:14:18,967 --> 00:14:21,300
Kiss my well-toned ass!
Get out!

319
00:14:21,533 --> 00:14:23,233
Excuse you!

320
00:14:23,433 --> 00:14:24,533
Are you talking to me?

321
00:14:24,533 --> 00:14:25,900
[ROS] Hey!

322
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:29,233
She may be too demure
to kick your ass, but I'm not!

323
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:33,000
You have ten seconds to get out
of my ward, Director Dumbass!

324
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,033
Out!

325
00:14:35,467 --> 00:14:36,533
[NOA] Stop talking.

326
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:37,900
Slow breaths.

327
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:39,567
- Camille.
- I'm on it!

328
00:14:39,567 --> 00:14:42,333
Rapid response to 503!

329
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:46,300
[DARK MUSIC PLAYS]

330
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,567
We're here! We're here!

331
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,300
One, two, three, four,
I declare a thumb war.

332
00:14:56,867 --> 00:14:58,167
This is getting sad.

333
00:14:58,433 --> 00:15:00,400
Don't act all high and mighty.
You're the one...

334
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,967
who stole my flowers,
and ruined my relationship.

335
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,033
You're the one
who wrote Noa's name.

336
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:07,033
Boop! 5-0!

337
00:15:07,033 --> 00:15:08,567
Denial's always easier, huh!

338
00:15:09,233 --> 00:15:10,333
I was distracted!

339
00:15:12,433 --> 00:15:13,467
Out of the way!

340
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:28,133
[NOA SIGHS]

341
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,033
I'm sorry, Mom.

342
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,033
[WIND WHOOSHES]

343
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,167
Don't be.

344
00:15:41,633 --> 00:15:43,400
Just trust Jane.

345
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:50,433
[JANE] Noa!

346
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:53,200
I've been looking for you.

347
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,200
How's Finny?

348
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,967
She'll live.

349
00:15:56,167 --> 00:15:58,933
What I can't explain is
who ordered the troponin.

350
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,200
Noa.

351
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:06,967
You've crossed the line.

352
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,500
Nurses don't order tests.

353
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,233
I'm sorry.

354
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,033
What would possess you
to do that?

355
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,667
You can't say
"based on your clinical eye,"

356
00:16:20,067 --> 00:16:21,967
because this is new to you.

357
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:25,200
Mom, please help me.
I'm sucking so bad right now.

358
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,233
Do not go there.

359
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:32,700
Do not use her
to get me to look away.

360
00:16:33,467 --> 00:16:35,300
Tess isn't here anymore.

361
00:16:37,533 --> 00:16:39,367
What if I told you she was?

362
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,567
Don't make this day any crazier.

363
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,433
She told me that every day
after nursing school,

364
00:16:51,433 --> 00:16:53,733
she'd see you
eating lunch by yourself.

365
00:16:54,267 --> 00:16:57,367
Not until she convinced a bunch
of Filipinos to invite you over.

366
00:16:58,567 --> 00:16:59,567
Okay, yeah...

367
00:17:00,167 --> 00:17:02,000
Well I wasn't the nicest person

368
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,967
when she was
my clinical instructor.

369
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:06,333
She could have told you that.

370
00:17:06,533 --> 00:17:08,700
I hate secrets, Jane.

371
00:17:09,267 --> 00:17:10,633
I hate not knowing stuff.

372
00:17:10,633 --> 00:17:11,567
But Mom?

373
00:17:11,567 --> 00:17:13,000
She never talked about work.

374
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,533
- Not until she--
- [STAMMERS]

375
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:16,433
Nurses hallucinate
from overworking.

376
00:17:16,467 --> 00:17:18,167
Don't do this to yourself.

377
00:17:19,267 --> 00:17:21,067
When you were
going over resumes...

378
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:23,400
Did my resume keep
popping up on your screen

379
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:25,167
until you recognized my name?

380
00:17:25,167 --> 00:17:26,767
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

381
00:17:27,433 --> 00:17:29,633
I know you checked
my address with Mom's.

382
00:17:30,133 --> 00:17:31,367
That's her fault.

383
00:17:31,367 --> 00:17:33,267
She taught me
how to use computer.

384
00:17:33,267 --> 00:17:34,267
How'd you...

385
00:17:34,267 --> 00:17:36,200
Mom saw you cry
in your office every night

386
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,500
during the pandemic.

387
00:17:40,367 --> 00:17:41,633
But when she passed,

388
00:17:42,733 --> 00:17:46,367
you cried so hard that
you vomited into your N95.

389
00:17:47,067 --> 00:17:49,167
Don't do this to me.

390
00:17:50,133 --> 00:17:51,600
[BREATH QUIVERS]

391
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:54,433
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

392
00:17:54,433 --> 00:17:56,200
I know you still talk to her.

393
00:17:57,467 --> 00:17:58,733
In your office.

394
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:02,333
Especially on nights
when you stay late.

395
00:18:05,433 --> 00:18:06,800
You sit there and talk to her

396
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,800
like she's still right
beside you.

397
00:18:11,267 --> 00:18:12,667
Because in those moments...

398
00:18:15,467 --> 00:18:16,500
She is.

399
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:25,367
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

400
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,567
[BREATH HITCHES]

401
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:34,700
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

402
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:38,400
Is she here?

403
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:42,300
Right now?

404
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,233
[EXHALES SHAKILY]

405
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:51,267
Tess.

406
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:57,200
[SNIFFLES, EXHALES DEEPLY]

407
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:02,767
You are still a pain
in my ass, lady.

408
00:19:02,767 --> 00:19:09,267
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

409
00:19:09,267 --> 00:19:10,600
Every Friday night...

410
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:14,867
We used to take
one shot of tequila.

411
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:19,367
- Just for the tea.
- I didn't tell her that part!

412
00:19:21,567 --> 00:19:23,467
She told me to trust you.

413
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:28,600
It was her experience
and clinical eye that...

414
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:32,300
...helped me save Finny's life.

415
00:19:33,433 --> 00:19:34,433
[EXHALES]

416
00:19:37,933 --> 00:19:39,233
You were right.

417
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:43,567
But the system does not allow
for this.

418
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:47,600
You have got to swear to me.

419
00:19:49,167 --> 00:19:50,367
And you, too, Tess.

420
00:19:52,933 --> 00:19:55,567
That you will remember
that we are nurses.

421
00:19:56,433 --> 00:19:58,233
She's right. She's right.

422
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:03,567
We do right by our patients,
but we do not diagnose.

423
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:04,833
Not on our own.

424
00:20:06,367 --> 00:20:08,533
You trust your team
to figure it out.

425
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:12,767
You trust me.

426
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:15,867
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

427
00:20:15,867 --> 00:20:18,467
It won't happen again.

428
00:20:21,567 --> 00:20:24,633
All that mentoring, and
this is what you remember?

429
00:20:24,633 --> 00:20:25,600
Tequila?

430
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:27,600
[GROANS SOFTLY]

431
00:20:30,267 --> 00:20:36,933
["THE DENIAL SONG"
BY JADE RICCIO PLAYING]

